From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Mon, 20 Jul 2026 00:46:12 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 54/58] web-app: add relays from list, contact scan or typed
 domain in Transports dialog
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

The Transports dialog previously offered only a QR scanner to add a transport.
This adds two ways to add a chatmail relay without a QR code:

- "Add from relay list…" opens the existing instant-onboarding relay picker
  (RelayPickerDialog, imported across the tree from WelcomeScreen — deliberate,
  moving it would break the patch stack). It lists the public relay directory,
  a "Relays your contacts use" section, and a free-text "Other relay…" field.
- The old button is relabeled "Scan relay QR code…" so its QR-only nature is
  obvious.

RelayPickerDialog is generalized with three optional props (selectedHost may be
empty = nothing selected, excludeHosts, contactRelays); the onboarding call site
is unchanged and still auto-probes the directory on open.

Privacy: the contact-derived relay section is never probed on open — probing
broadcasts contact mail hostnames to the bridge operator, so reachability is
only measured when the user clicks "Measure ping", which then re-sorts that
section by latency. The directory section keeps its on-open auto-probe.

contactRelayCandidates aggregates contact domains (getContactIds/getContactsByIds)
purely and is unit-tested. A contact's mail domain need not be a chatmail relay;
adding a non-chatmail domain fails loudly through the existing error alert, which
is the accepted design.

Picking the default-tagged relay row now signs up with the instance's configured
QR verbatim (instanceDefaultChatmailQr, matching onboarding) instead of rebuilding
"dcaccount:" + host, so an operator's URL-form or path-bearing SLOTHFUL_DEFAULT_CHATMAIL
account-creation endpoint survives; the confirm dialog still shows the bare host.

All new strings are hardcoded English, matching this fork's relay-picker patch
convention (no locale files touched).

Co-authored-by: Claude Fable 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>
